The paper deals with active learning and decision-making in a Bayesian framework, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The applications of the proposed method are in drug and materials discovery, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
